<br>
Nuclear power and radiation run amok! It's a plot line which has figured in many films - from B-movies to Academy Award winners. You may recall how one of the earliest scripts had Godzilla mutated and summoned from the depths by the atomic bomb tests of the '40s and '50s. The following film list includes sci-fi, adventures and dramas. How many do you remember?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.godzilla.com/assets/foot.gif"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.pbs.org/wgbh/pages/frontline/shows/reaction/interact/hollywood.html">www.pbs.org/wgbh/pages/frontline/shows/reaction/interact/hollywood.html</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
<br>
First Yank Into Tokyo -- 1945<br>
American, War<br>
Director: Gordon Douglas<br>
Cast includes: Tom Neal, Barbara Hale, Marc Cramer, Richard Loo<br>
Synopsis: Of interest as the first Hollywood film to involve the subject of nuclear warfare. An American poses as a Japanese soldier to rescue a nuclear scientist POW.<br>
(Available on videocassette)<br>
<br>
<br>
The World, the Flesh, and the Devil -- 1959<br>
American, Science Fiction<br>
Director: Ranald MacDougall<br>
Cast includes: Harry Belafonte, Inger Stevens, Mel Ferrer<br>
Synopsis: Belafonte and Stevens are the only survivors of a global-scale nuclear accident.<br>
(Available on videocassette)<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
The Horror of Party Beach -- 1964<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.pbs.org/wgbh/pages/frontline/shows/reaction/art/hop.gif"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
American, Horror<br>
Director: Del Tenney<br>
Cast includes: John Scott, Alice Lyon, Allen Laurel, Marilyn Clark<br>
Synopsis: One of the first anti-nuclear films. The dumping of radioactive waste off the coast of Connecticut turns a dreamy beach day into a nightmare when creepy monsters invade the surf.<br>
(Black and white, available on videocassette)<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Red Alert -- 1977<br>
American, Drama<br>
Director: William Hale<br>
Cast includes: William Devane, Michael Brandon, Adrienne Barbeau, Ralph Waite, David<br>
Hayward, M. Emmet Walsh<br>
Synopsis: A thriller stemming from an accident at a nuclear power plant. Based on the novel Paradigm Red by Harold King. (Available on videocassette)<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
The Chosen -- 1978<br>
American/Italian, Horror/Science Fiction<br>
Director: Alberto De Martino<br>
Cast includes: Kirk Douglas, Agostina Belli, Simon Ward, Anthony Quayle<br>
Synopsis: A nuclear power executive discovers his son is plotting to destroy the world by utilizing nuclear power.<br>
Originally titled HOLOCAUST 2000.<br>
(Available on videocassette)<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
The China Syndrome -- 1979<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.pbs.org/wgbh/pages/frontline/shows/reaction/art/china.gif"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
Fonda in 'The China Syndrome'. <br>
<br>
American, Drama<br>
Director: James Bridges<br>
Cast includes: Jane Fonda, Jack Lemmon, Michael Douglas, Scott Brady, James Hampton,Peter Donat, Wilford Brimley James Karen<br>
Synopsis: Reporters Jane Fonda and Michael Douglas inadvertently film an accident taking place at a nuclear power plant and confront the industry's cover-up. (The title refers to nuclear jargon for the worst conceivable reactor accident: the reactor core overheats and melts through the plant floor, theoretically all the way through the earth to China.) (Available on videocassette)<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Island Claws -- 1980<br>
American, Science Fiction<br>
Director: Hernan Cardenas<br>
Cast includes: Robert Lansing, Steve Hanks, Nita Talbot, Barry Nelson<br>
Synopsis: A leak at a Florida nuclear reactor turns crabs into giant killers!<br>
(Available on videocassette)<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
The Children -- 1980<br>
American, Horror<br>
Director: Max Kalmanowicz<br>
Cast includes: Martin Shakar, Gil Rogers, Gale Garnett, Jesse Abrams<br>
Synopsis: School children become radioactive when a toxic gas from a nuclear power plant invades their school bus. It gives the kids a weird symptom: anyone they hug burns up.<br>
(Available on videocassette)<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Chain Reaction -- 1980<br>
Australian Adventure<br>
Director: Ian Barry<br>
Cast includes: Steve Bisley, Arna-Maria Winchester, Ross Thompson, Ralph Cotterill<br>
Synopsis: A thriller about the aftermath of a nuclear plant accident that contaminates a worker and a two civilians, who then take on the industry. (Check out the cameo appearance by Mel Gibson as a car mechanic.)<br>
(Available on videocassette)<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Stronger Than the Sun -- 1980<br>
British, Drama<br>
Director: Michael Apted<br>
Cast includes: Francesca Annis, Tom Bell<br>
Synopsis: A nuclear power plant worker tries to expose a radioactive leak. <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
No Nukes -- 1980<br>
American, Musical/Documentary<br>
Director: Julian Schlossberg, Danny Goldberg, Anthony Potenza<br>
Cast includes: Jackson Browne, Crosby, Stills and Nash, The Doobie Brothers, John Hall, Gil,Scott-Heron, Bonnie Raitt,<br>
Carly Simon, Bruce Springsteen, James Taylor, Jesse Colin Young, Jane Fonda<br>
Synopsis: Rock stars convene to protest nuclear power. Includes 1950s pro-nuclear video clip. (Also known as THE MUSE CONCERT: NO NUKES)<br>
(Available on videocassette)<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
The Plutonium Incident -- 1980<br>
American, Drama<br>
Director:Richard Michaels<br>
Cast includes: Janet Margolin, Bo Hopkins, Joseph Campanella, Powers Boothe, Bibi Besch, Nicholas Pryor<br>
Synopsis: Taking a cue from the Karen Silkwood story, this film features an activist struggling to spur employees to action after a power plant accident. The company tries to intimidate her.<br>
(Available on videocassette)<br>
<br>
<br>
Human Highway -- 1982<br>
American, Drama<br>
Director: Bernard Shakey (Neil Young), Dean Stockwell<br>
Cast includes: Neil Young, Russ Tamblyn, Dennis Hopper, Sally Kirkland, Dean Stockwell, Charlotte Stewart, Devo<br>
Synopsis: A zany anti-nuke comedy, including Neil Young concert footage and a glowing, radioactive rock band (Devo) contaminated from a nearby plant.<br>
<br>
<br>
The Being -- 1983<br>
American , Horror/humor<br>
Director: Jackie Kong<br>
Cast includes :Martin Landau, Jose Ferrer, Dorothy Malone, Ruth Buzzi<br>
Synopsis: <br>
A nuclear waste site gives birth to a creature that terrorizes an Idaho town. <br>
(Available on videocassette)<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Silkwood -- 1983<br>
American, Biography<br>
Director: Mike Nichols<br>
Cast includes: Meryl Streep, Kurt Russell, Cher, Craig T. Nelson, Diana Scarwid, Fred Ward, Ron Silver, Charles Hallahan, Josef Sommer, Sudie Bond, Henderson Forsythe, E. Katherine Kerr, Bruce McGill, David Strathairn, M. Emmet Walsh, Ray Baker, Tess Harper, Anthony Heald<br>
Synopsis: Whistleblowers face an uphill battle against an Oklahoma nuclear parts factory when they try to expose unsafe practices, and when one employee becomes contaminated. <br>
Based on the story of Karen Silkwood.<br>
(Available on videocassette)<br>
<br>
<br>
*Note: Check out the true, fact-based story of Karen Silkwood.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
In Our Hands --1984<br>
American, Documentary<br>
Director: none credited<br>
Synopsis: Documentary about the June 1982 anti-nuclear rally in New York City. <br>
Includes speeches, music, and appearances by Helen Caldicott and Benjamin Spock, Pete Seeger, Carly Simon, Peter, Paul &amp; Mary, Holly Near, Roy Scheider, Ellen Burstyn, Jill Clayburgh, Orson Welles, Meryl Streep, and others.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Choke Canyon -- 1986<br>
American, Action/Adventure<br>
Director: Chuck Bail<br>
Cast includes: Stephen Collins, Janet Julian, Lance Henriksen, Bo Svenson<br>
Synopsis: A heroic physicist tries to stop the dumping of nuclear waste the day before Haley's Comet is due to pass by the earth. Includes aerial stuntwork.<br>
(Available on videocassette)<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Class of Nuke 'Em High -- 1986<br>
American, Horror/Comedy<br>
Director: Richard Haines, Samuel Weil<br>
Cast includes: Janelle Brady, Gilbert Brenton, Robert Prichard, R.L. Ryan<br>
Synopsis: A nuclear waste spill near a New Jersey high school spawns monsters and mutates a few straight-A students. <br>
(Available on videocassette)<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Dead End Kids -- 1986<br>
American, Comedy/Drama<br>
Director: JoAnne Akalaitis<br>
Cast Includes: Ellen McElduff, Ruth Maleczech, George Bartenieff, David Brisbin<br>
Synopsis: The complete title is DEAD END KIDS: A STORY OF NUCLEAR POWER. The history of nuclear power is presented in a dramatic narrative. Adapted from an<br>
off-Broadway production by Mabou Mines. Music by David Byrne and Philip Glass.<br>
(Color and B&amp;W)<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Chernobyl: The Final Warning -- 1991<br>
Russian/American<br>
Director: Anthony Page<br>
Cast includes: Jon Voight, Jason Robards , Sammi Davis, Annette Crosbie<br>
Synopsis: Filmed on location, the docudrama centers around Robert Gale, the California surgeon credited for helping victims and Armand Hammer, the business magnate. Voight's<br>
first television appearance in 22 years. <br>
(Available on videocassette as FINAL WARNING)<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
The Naked Gun 2: The Smell of Fear -- 1991<br>
American, Comedy<br>
Director: David Zucker<br>
Cast includes: Leslie Nielsen, Priscilla Presley, George Kennedy, O.J. Simpson, Robert Goulet <br>
Synopsis: Big-wigs from the oil, coal, and nuclear power industries conspire to prevent the US from adopting a new energy policy. Frank Drebin comes to the rescue.<br>
(Available on videocassette)<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Touch and Die -- 1991<br>
American, Thriller<br>
Available on videocassette<br>
Director: Piernico Solinas<br>
Cast includes: Renee Estevez, Martin Sheen, David Birney, Franco Nero<br>
Synopsis: A journalist follows the trail of plutonium thieves and uncovers a scheme in which nuclear power advocates funnel money into the coffers of a pro-nuclear candidate.<br>
(Available on videocassette)<br>
